10_large_angle_deg


  1. Question

    Which graph shows a 664\(^\circ\) angle in standard position?



    1. A
    2. B
    3. C
    4. D
    5. E
    6. F
    7. G
    8. H

    Solution

    The given angle is 664\(^\circ\). The angle is positive, so the angle rotates counterclockwise.

    Notice if we divide 664 by 360 we get 1 with a remainder of 304. So, rotate 1 full times and then also rotate by 304\(^\circ\).

    Notice that 304\(^\circ\) is between 270\(^\circ\) and 360\(^\circ\), so it’ll need between 3 and 4 quarter turns after the 1 full turns (all counterclockwise). That puts the terminal side in quadrant 4 (quadrant IV).

    1. A
    2. B

    6. F
    7. G
    8. H

    Solution
